			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2299962">
									

<p>Yes I understand that (although &quot;Django&quot; is more properly a nickname). I am saying that Romani usually aren't named &quot;Bridge&quot;, &quot;Lurk&quot; had been out of fashion for a long time and that &quot;Aleksandar Foxx&quot; sounds way too much like a comic book character (also what language doesn't have an &quot;x&quot; for &quot;Alexander&quot; but does for &quot;Fox&quot;?). One person with an unlikely name is maybe cool, but not everyone&#8230;</p>
<p>Also while real life can get away with not bothering to be realistic, fiction can afford no such luxuries. Again though, this appears to be just my problem, so no worries!</p>

