					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250576" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1432228319 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 May 2015 17:11</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2300225">
									

<p>Real life gets away with being unbelievable because it is undeniably real.</p>
<p>Edit: Or to put it another way, in fiction the author controls every element present. If something doesn't contribute to theme then you should consider not including it, especially if it is a distraction. Weird names make me analyze why they are there. Either I am missing something or these aren't there for a reason. So instead of enjoying the story and thinking about what the author wants me to think about, I am thinking about this. Hence, distracting.</p>

							</div>

								
