														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2300236">
									

<p>If memory serves, US TV and film can only use a name if there are less than one or more than three instances of that exact name in the country. So names tend to be either quite common or extremely uncommon.</p>
<p>Fun fact: When the original <em>Star Trek</em> aired, there was a US Navy officer named James Kirk who had just been promoted. Proof that fact can be stranger than fiction&#8230;</p>

